headline: Shareholder Probes of MOH Cost Assumptions Could Be A Game Changer For Molina Healthcare
summary: In recent months, Molina Healthcare has faced shareholder class action investigations alleging that management misrepresented medical cost trends, premium rate alignment, and the sustainability of its financial guidance for fiscal 2025. These legal challenges highlight how sensitive Molina’s business model may be to assumptions around healthcare utilization and the transparency of its cost projections. headline: Democrats Pounce as Congress Allows Obamacare Premiums to Spike
summary: Health care premiums for more than 20 million Americans will, on average, more than double in 2026, which risks putting insurance out of reach for many voters already concerned about the costs of housing, groceries, utilities and other expenses.  When lawmakers return to the Capitol next month, they have less than two weeks to resolve the issue before open enrollment ends Jan. 15.  Amid fierce Republican infighting, Democrats are already declaring victory.
